<div class="container narrow-container mt-4">

    <h1 class="mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p>
        Acebook is committed to respecting your privacy and protecting your personal information.
        This page explains what data we collect, how we use it, and the choices you have while using our platform.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-4">Information We Collect</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Account details</strong> such as your name, email address, and password.</li>
        <li><strong>Session information</strong> to keep you securely logged in.</li>
        <li><strong>User‑generated content</strong> including posts, comments, and friend requests.</li>
        <li><strong>Basic usage data</strong> to help us understand how the site is used.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        We do <strong>not</strong> sell your data or share it with third‑party advertisers.
        All information is used solely to support and improve the Acebook experience.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-4">How We Use Your Information</h3>
    <p>Your information is used to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Authenticate your account and manage your session.</li>
        <li>Display your posts, comments, and interactions.</li>
        <li>Connect you with friends and manage friend requests.</li>
        <li>Improve the performance and reliability of Acebook.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="mt-4">Cookies</h3>
    <p>
        Acebook uses cookies to keep you logged in and support essential site functionality.
        You can disable cookies in your browser, but some features may stop working.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-4">Data Security</h3>
    <p>
        We take reasonable steps to protect your information, including secure password hashing
        and restricted access to user data. While no system is perfect, we work to keep Acebook safe and reliable.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-4">Your Choices</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Update your account information at any time.</li>
        <li>Delete posts or comments you’ve created.</li>
        <li>Log out to end your session.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="mt-4">Updates to This Policy</h3>
    <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated date.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-4 text-muted">
        Last updated: February 2026
    </p>
</div>

